WEBVTT

00:09.542 --> 00:19.626
♪♪♪

00:20.250 --> 00:22.542
(Workers and merchants

00:20.250 --> 00:22.542
speaking in French)

00:22.584 --> 00:23.876
(Wagon wheels creek)

00:25.375 --> 00:27.334
Malcolm: So we make a deal

00:25.375 --> 00:27.334
with this Lake Walkers tribe,

00:27.375 --> 00:28.751
then what?

00:28.792 --> 00:30.834
We canna handle

00:28.792 --> 00:30.834
that kind of volume.

00:30.876 --> 00:32.792
We haven't got the men for it.

00:32.834 --> 00:34.459
- The men can be purchased.

00:32.834 --> 00:34.459
- What with?

00:34.500 --> 00:36.876
When our ship sunk it took

00:34.500 --> 00:36.876
all of our capital with it -

00:36.918 --> 00:38.584
ten thousand pelts.

00:38.626 --> 00:39.834
We donna have a pot to piss in!

00:39.876 --> 00:41.834
- He makes a good fuckin' point

00:39.876 --> 00:41.834
there, Douglas.

00:41.876 --> 00:44.626
Douglas: There is a new man in

00:41.876 --> 00:44.626
town, an American Samuel Grant.

00:44.667 --> 00:46.042
He's rich and he's hungry.

00:46.083 --> 00:47.250
We approach him.

00:47.292 --> 00:48.792
Malcolm: An investor?

00:47.292 --> 00:48.792
- Aye!

00:48.834 --> 00:51.167
We tell him we're about to

00:48.834 --> 00:51.167
secure the Lake Walker trade.

00:51.209 --> 00:53.167
Malcolm: It's just more fuckin'

00:51.209 --> 00:53.167
debt!

00:53.209 --> 00:55.375
I'd rather pull up stakes

00:53.209 --> 00:55.375
and go back to Scotland

00:55.417 --> 00:57.375
than jump into some

00:55.417 --> 00:57.375
ill-thought-out

00:57.417 --> 00:58.584
new fuckin' scheme!

00:58.626 --> 01:00.250
- I agree. He's fuckin' right!

01:00.292 --> 01:02.459
Douglas: Malcolm, Cedric,

01:00.292 --> 01:02.459
we're bankrupt!

01:02.500 --> 01:04.542
We owe thousands

01:02.500 --> 01:04.542
to our creditors.

01:04.584 --> 01:06.334
We could be thrown in prison

01:04.584 --> 01:06.334
at any moment.

01:06.375 --> 01:07.918
We cannot just walk away.

01:07.959 --> 01:10.042
- Who's gonna fuckin' stop us?

01:10.083 --> 01:11.584
Huh?

01:11.626 --> 01:14.167
- I donna like it either,

01:14.209 --> 01:15.792
but we're up against it.

01:15.834 --> 01:17.417
We have to make a move right now

01:17.459 --> 01:19.876
or the Low River Company

01:17.459 --> 01:19.876
is finished.

01:21.000 --> 01:22.584
Cedric can leave tomorrow

01:21.000 --> 01:22.584
for the North,

01:22.626 --> 01:25.500
make contact with

01:22.626 --> 01:25.500
the Lake Walkers.

01:25.542 --> 01:27.667
If we establish trade

01:25.542 --> 01:27.667
with them,

01:27.709 --> 01:30.834
this could make us richer

01:27.709 --> 01:30.834
than we ever imagined.

01:34.000 --> 01:37.042
- (Breathing hard)

01:34.000 --> 01:37.042
(Twigs snap, brush rustles)

01:38.751 --> 01:41.667
(Pounding footsteps)

01:41.709 --> 01:43.042
- (Grunts with effort,

01:41.709 --> 01:43.042
breathing hard)

01:43.083 --> 01:44.918
(Twigs snap, brush rustles)

01:44.959 --> 01:47.125
(Grunts with effort)

01:47.167 --> 01:48.792
(Breathing hard)

01:48.834 --> 01:49.959
(Violent thud) (Grunts)

01:50.000 --> 01:51.876
- (Growls)

01:52.000 --> 01:53.792
I'm going to kill you.

01:53.834 --> 01:56.334
Too late. You're already dead.

01:56.375 --> 01:58.500
You never win at this game.

01:58.542 --> 01:59.959
I want to be the hunter

01:58.542 --> 01:59.959
next time.

02:03.459 --> 02:05.792
You lose when you're

02:03.459 --> 02:05.792
the hunter, too.

02:05.834 --> 02:06.667
Not this time.

02:07.542 --> 02:09.876
(Gunshot booms, blood splatters)

02:09.918 --> 02:11.542
(Gasps in pain) (Heavy thump)

02:11.584 --> 02:13.584
(Brush rustles)

02:13.626 --> 02:15.584
(Gunshot booms)

02:13.626 --> 02:15.584
- (Grunts in pain)

02:15.626 --> 02:17.292
(Moans)

02:17.334 --> 02:18.792
(Violent punch) (Hard thump)

02:18.834 --> 02:20.542
- (Grunting pants)

02:20.584 --> 02:22.250
You wee shit.

02:22.292 --> 02:25.209
- The other one got away!

02:25.250 --> 02:27.042
Who's this?

02:27.083 --> 02:28.667
Cedric: He's Kitchi,

02:28.709 --> 02:31.584
Grandson of the

02:28.709 --> 02:31.584
Lake Walker Chief twat.

02:32.626 --> 02:34.667
If his people want

02:32.626 --> 02:34.667
to see him again,

02:34.709 --> 02:36.834
those fuckers are gonna

02:34.709 --> 02:36.834
have to deal with me

02:36.876 --> 02:38.375
and my brothers.

02:38.417 --> 02:40.334
Now come on. (Sniffs)

02:40.375 --> 02:41.876
(Grunts with effort)

02:41.918 --> 02:44.542
(Fire crackles)

02:44.584 --> 02:46.042
- (Sniffs)

02:48.417 --> 02:49.626
(Hard thumps)

02:50.751 --> 02:52.626
(Desperate clawing)

02:52.667 --> 02:53.959
(Hard thump)

02:52.667 --> 02:53.959
- Chogan!

02:54.000 --> 02:55.626
- (Gasps for air)

02:55.667 --> 02:57.209
Kitchi!

02:57.250 --> 02:58.459
They took him.

02:58.500 --> 02:59.542
Who took him?

02:59.584 --> 03:02.584
The White Men.

03:02.626 --> 03:06.167
They wore the colored sash.

03:02.626 --> 03:06.167
Red and blue.

03:08.209 --> 03:09.500
(Gasps for air)

03:11.417 --> 03:21.417
♪♪♪

03:24.667 --> 03:26.292
(Native singing)

03:26.334 --> 03:36.334
♪♪♪

03:41.250 --> 03:43.417
(Native singing)

03:43.459 --> 03:56.542
♪♪♪

04:01.500 --> 04:03.792
- Something's happenin'.

04:03.834 --> 04:05.334
They're moving out.

04:05.375 --> 04:07.125
- (Mumbles quietly)

04:09.292 --> 04:11.125
Mr. Harp.

04:11.167 --> 04:14.792
Mr. Harp, have...

04:11.167 --> 04:14.792
have mercy on a poor priest!

04:14.834 --> 04:17.417
Maybe just a drop of wine?

04:14.834 --> 04:17.417
(Hard slap)

04:17.459 --> 04:19.250
Ah! Just a minute!

04:19.292 --> 04:21.751
Wait, no, no! No!

04:21.792 --> 04:23.250
No!

04:23.292 --> 04:26.250
- He's sufferin' -

04:23.292 --> 04:26.250
lack of drink.

04:26.292 --> 04:28.709
If you kill him you'd just

04:26.292 --> 04:28.709
be doing him a favor.

04:28.751 --> 04:30.792
I told ya, I'm here

04:28.751 --> 04:30.792
to make my fortune.

04:30.834 --> 04:32.959
I have many skills.

04:30.834 --> 04:32.959
I'm a quick learner.

04:33.000 --> 04:34.250
I can help ya.

04:34.292 --> 04:36.250
You wouldn't hurt a fellow

04:34.292 --> 04:36.250
Irishman, would you?

04:36.292 --> 04:38.292
- Do I look like

04:36.292 --> 04:38.292
an Irishman to you?

04:38.334 --> 04:39.792
- I was told your father was.

04:39.834 --> 04:42.167
Harp: Were you told I was

04:39.834 --> 04:42.167
raised by a Cree mother?

04:42.209 --> 04:44.834
(Knife scrapes)

04:42.209 --> 04:44.834
Michael: Whatcha doin' there?

04:44.876 --> 04:46.417
- Can't rush a thing like this,

04:46.459 --> 04:48.751
skin won't peel right,

04:46.459 --> 04:48.751
ruins the hide.

04:48.792 --> 04:50.709
(Metal clanks)

04:48.792 --> 04:50.709
- Oh Jesus!

04:50.751 --> 04:52.834
I've told you everythin'.

04:50.751 --> 04:52.834
I swear, the truth!

04:52.876 --> 04:54.334
(Panicked breathing)

04:55.626 --> 04:58.000
- What's your connection

04:55.626 --> 04:58.000
with Lord Benton?

04:58.042 --> 05:00.167
- Nothin'. I told ya I came

04:58.042 --> 05:00.167
over on his ship.

05:01.250 --> 05:03.500
He hates your guts.

05:01.250 --> 05:03.500
That's all I know, that's--

05:03.542 --> 05:05.125
(Skin sizzles, pained shout)

05:05.167 --> 05:07.918
All right!

05:05.167 --> 05:07.918
I made a deal with him!

05:07.959 --> 05:10.042
I made a deal with him!

05:07.959 --> 05:10.042
He made me an offer, he said,

05:10.083 --> 05:12.125
he said I needed to come

05:10.083 --> 05:12.125
find ya, Declan Harp he said,

05:12.167 --> 05:14.292
and he said I had to tell him

05:12.167 --> 05:14.292
where you were

05:14.334 --> 05:16.334
and how many people was here.

05:14.334 --> 05:16.334
(Panicked breathing)

05:16.375 --> 05:18.334
- And what did he tell

05:16.375 --> 05:18.334
you about me?

05:18.375 --> 05:20.918
- That you worked together.

05:18.375 --> 05:20.918
That you had a disagreement.

05:20.959 --> 05:22.292
(Panicked breathing)

05:22.334 --> 05:24.626
That you've become wild.

05:24.667 --> 05:26.375
- And he offered you what?

05:26.417 --> 05:29.250
Money? Land?

05:29.292 --> 05:31.042
(Fire crackles)

05:31.083 --> 05:33.083
- (Gasps) There's a girl!

05:31.083 --> 05:33.083
There's a girl!

05:33.125 --> 05:34.209
I love her.

05:34.250 --> 05:36.083
Her name is Clenna.

05:36.125 --> 05:38.542
Benton said he'd hang

05:36.125 --> 05:38.542
her if I didn't do it.

05:38.584 --> 05:40.542
(Fire crackles)

05:40.584 --> 05:45.083
♪♪♪

05:45.125 --> 05:47.083
What, what are you doin'?

05:45.125 --> 05:47.083
What are you doin'?

05:47.125 --> 05:49.209
(Loud slice) (Gasps, pants)

05:49.250 --> 05:53.209
- You trust Benton's word

05:49.250 --> 05:53.209
your girl's as good as dead.

05:53.250 --> 05:55.918
I hope you paddle

05:53.250 --> 05:55.918
better than you lie.

05:58.417 --> 06:00.292
(Crickets chirp, loons warble)

06:00.334 --> 06:02.751
- (Grimaces)

06:00.334 --> 06:02.751
(Fire crackles)

06:04.417 --> 06:05.876
(Approaching footsteps)

06:05.918 --> 06:07.542
(Tent flap rustles)

06:09.417 --> 06:12.042
They weren't soldiers, they

06:09.417 --> 06:12.042
were White People. Europeans.

06:12.083 --> 06:14.083
Red and blue tartans.

06:14.125 --> 06:16.667
That means Low River men.

06:16.709 --> 06:20.792
The Brown Brothers

06:16.709 --> 06:20.792
want our trade

06:20.834 --> 06:22.459
and this is how they negotiate?

06:22.500 --> 06:24.834
Machk,

06:24.876 --> 06:27.834
we do not know this for sure.

06:27.876 --> 06:29.918
I will gather a group

06:27.876 --> 06:29.918
of warriors

06:29.959 --> 06:31.751
and I will free him.

06:31.792 --> 06:35.834
No. You will wait.

06:35.876 --> 06:41.125
The Low River men have too much

06:35.876 --> 06:41.125
to lose in conflict with us.

06:41.167 --> 06:47.667
Right now, I want you

06:41.167 --> 06:47.667
to be patient and do nothing.

06:47.709 --> 06:49.292
- (Unhappy grunt)

06:49.334 --> 06:51.042
(Tent flap rustles)

06:51.083 --> 06:52.417
- (Angry hiss)

06:52.459 --> 06:54.584
(Townspeople chatter,

06:52.459 --> 06:54.584
seagulls cry)

06:54.626 --> 06:56.626
(Heavy shuffling footsteps)

06:56.667 --> 06:58.626
(Townspeople chatter)

06:59.876 --> 07:01.459
(Chickens cluck)

07:02.876 --> 07:04.834
(Wagon clatters)

07:04.876 --> 07:06.918
(Townspeople chatter)

07:06.959 --> 07:09.000
(Steadying exhales)

07:09.042 --> 07:10.834
(Heavy shuffling footsteps)

07:10.876 --> 07:13.042
(Wagon squeaks)

07:13.083 --> 07:14.751
(Heavy shuffling footsteps)

07:16.751 --> 07:19.125
- This is not a whorehouse.

07:19.167 --> 07:20.834
You do not entertain these men.

07:20.876 --> 07:23.167
You serve them food and drink,

07:20.876 --> 07:23.167
is that clear?

07:23.209 --> 07:24.626
- Clear.

07:24.667 --> 07:26.751
- And you listen, carefully,

07:26.792 --> 07:29.125
every word, every conversation.

07:26.792 --> 07:29.125
- Miss Emberly...

07:29.167 --> 07:31.667
- I want to know what's being

07:29.167 --> 07:31.667
said and who said it.

07:31.709 --> 07:33.876
I will reward you for

07:31.709 --> 07:33.876
every piece of information--

07:33.918 --> 07:36.083
- Miss Emberly,

07:33.918 --> 07:36.083
it's Captain Chesterfield.

07:36.125 --> 07:37.334
(Shuffling footsteps)

07:37.375 --> 07:39.167
(Patrons talk loudly)

07:39.209 --> 07:40.626
- Whiskey. Double.

07:41.792 --> 07:44.125
- Good lord. Come to the back.

07:44.167 --> 07:46.334
(Shuffling footsteps)

07:46.375 --> 07:48.083
(Patrons talk loudly)

07:48.125 --> 07:49.751
(Water splashes)

07:52.584 --> 07:54.125
(Liquor sloshes)

07:55.167 --> 07:57.584
- (Grimaces)

07:55.167 --> 07:57.584
- Keep still.

07:58.918 --> 08:01.250
- (Sighs)

08:01.292 --> 08:03.167
- What the hell happened to you?

08:03.209 --> 08:05.125
- (Swallows)

08:06.626 --> 08:09.250
Didn't see.

08:09.292 --> 08:11.626
Struck from behind.

08:11.667 --> 08:13.792
Three good men murdered.

08:13.834 --> 08:15.751
(Grimaces, sighs)

08:15.792 --> 08:18.375
- You've been living in the

08:15.792 --> 08:18.375
safety of London too long.

08:18.417 --> 08:19.918
Getting careless.

08:19.959 --> 08:21.876
- Mind your words, woman!

08:22.959 --> 08:24.959
- And the boy? Michael?

08:26.500 --> 08:28.125
- He's gone.

08:28.167 --> 08:30.459
Likely dead.

08:30.500 --> 08:31.876
(Water splashes)

08:31.918 --> 08:34.125
- I don't imagine Lord Benton

08:31.918 --> 08:34.125
will be too happy

08:34.167 --> 08:35.334
to hear about all this.

08:35.375 --> 08:37.334
(Hard slap)

08:35.375 --> 08:37.334
- Watch it!

08:37.375 --> 08:43.250
♪♪♪

08:43.292 --> 08:46.709
- And what of our drunken

08:43.292 --> 08:46.709
Governor, Mr. Threadwell?

08:46.751 --> 08:49.709
He must be feeling the pressure

08:46.751 --> 08:49.709
with Lord Benton's arrival.

08:49.751 --> 08:52.125
- I expect Threadwell

08:49.751 --> 08:52.125
will be on the next ship

08:52.167 --> 08:53.876
bound for England.

08:55.792 --> 08:58.500
- Leaving a vacancy that

08:55.792 --> 08:58.500
needs to be filled.

08:58.542 --> 09:01.125
Don't move your head.

09:01.167 --> 09:03.417
It occurs to me that...

09:05.417 --> 09:08.792
with my help you could make

09:05.417 --> 09:08.792
an excellent Governor.

09:09.918 --> 09:12.459
- And you would stand

09:09.918 --> 09:12.459
to gain what?

09:14.500 --> 09:16.584
- A business partner.

09:16.626 --> 09:18.500
There, finished.

09:24.751 --> 09:26.375
- I could have done this myself.

09:26.417 --> 09:28.417
- That's the idea.

09:29.918 --> 09:31.292
You should go.

09:31.334 --> 09:33.584
If Lord Benton finds out that

09:31.334 --> 09:33.584
you stopped for a drink

09:33.626 --> 09:37.209
on your way back, you'll get

09:33.626 --> 09:37.209
worse than a scalp wound.

09:38.667 --> 09:41.250
(Liquor sloshes)

09:42.918 --> 09:45.167
Give that partnership

09:42.918 --> 09:45.167
some thought.

09:46.876 --> 09:48.375
(Receding footsteps)

09:49.417 --> 09:51.250
(Low hum of patron chatter)

09:53.250 --> 09:55.292
Benton: You've had a rough

09:53.250 --> 09:55.292
go of it, Threadwell,

09:55.334 --> 09:57.292
that's more than clear.

09:57.334 --> 09:59.667
- Ah, well the winters, my Lord.

09:59.709 --> 10:01.500
Very harsh,

10:01.542 --> 10:03.876
longer than anticipated,

10:01.542 --> 10:03.876
colder...

10:03.918 --> 10:05.500
- Yes, indeed.

10:05.542 --> 10:08.584
Threadwell: The French and the

10:05.542 --> 10:08.584
natives have been plaguing us,

10:08.626 --> 10:11.709
but I would say

10:08.626 --> 10:11.709
we've acquitted ourselves

10:11.751 --> 10:14.167
rather well under

10:11.751 --> 10:14.167
the circumstances.

10:14.209 --> 10:17.375
- And you will be rewarded

10:14.209 --> 10:17.375
properly for your work here,

10:17.417 --> 10:19.459
I will personally see to it.

10:19.500 --> 10:21.042
In the meantime,

10:21.083 --> 10:23.876
I've arranged for a cabin

10:21.083 --> 10:23.876
for you here on the ship.

10:23.918 --> 10:26.167
- But I have my residence

10:23.918 --> 10:26.167
on the outskirts of town.

10:26.209 --> 10:28.250
I'd be much more comfortable

10:26.209 --> 10:28.250
there, thank you.

10:28.292 --> 10:30.459
(Door opens)

10:28.292 --> 10:30.459
- I'm afraid I have to insist.

10:30.500 --> 10:32.459
- Now just one moment.

10:32.500 --> 10:34.709
- You'll be quite comfortable.

10:34.751 --> 10:37.751
- (Gasps) How dare you?!

10:34.751 --> 10:37.751
You have no right!

10:37.792 --> 10:39.834
Benton! You will regret this!

10:39.876 --> 10:41.542
Unhand me! I say!

10:43.083 --> 10:45.125
Benton, unhand me!

10:45.167 --> 10:47.959
Unhand me now! How dare you?!

10:48.000 --> 10:49.667
(Approaching footsteps)

10:49.709 --> 10:51.125
(Jacket rustles)

10:51.167 --> 10:53.250
- Captain Chesterfield,

10:53.292 --> 10:56.375
it seems you stand

10:53.292 --> 10:56.375
before me empty-handed.

10:56.417 --> 10:58.334
- Sir... I was ambushed,

11:00.417 --> 11:02.209
my men murdered.

11:02.250 --> 11:04.959
- A decorated English captain.

11:05.000 --> 11:06.584
Pathetic.

11:07.834 --> 11:11.334
I suspect the boy's being eaten

11:07.834 --> 11:11.334
by wolves as we speak,

11:11.375 --> 11:13.375
but perhaps not.

11:13.417 --> 11:16.667
If by some miracle

11:13.417 --> 11:16.667
he's managed to stay alive,

11:16.709 --> 11:20.334
you may yet have a chance

11:16.709 --> 11:20.334
to redeem yourself.

11:23.375 --> 11:24.918
Shall we?

11:26.125 --> 11:27.626
♪♪♪

11:27.667 --> 11:29.083
(Loud crunching bang)

11:29.125 --> 11:30.667
- (Violent gurgling)

11:30.709 --> 11:35.167
♪♪♪

11:35.209 --> 11:37.584
- For the past 100 years,

11:37.626 --> 11:40.959
we have dominated the rivers

11:37.626 --> 11:40.959
and shores of Hudson's Bay.

11:43.000 --> 11:45.375
Yet now we find ourselves...

11:46.584 --> 11:48.500
challenged,

11:49.584 --> 11:51.584
losing territory,

11:51.626 --> 11:53.334
profits down,

11:53.375 --> 11:55.709
and unable to staunch

11:53.375 --> 11:55.709
the bleeding.

11:57.459 --> 12:00.250
The most powerful navy

11:57.459 --> 12:00.250
in the world

12:00.292 --> 12:02.375
run ragged by men in canoes.

12:03.459 --> 12:04.626
(Waves lap)

12:06.876 --> 12:08.834
The Scots,

12:08.876 --> 12:10.542
the French,

12:10.584 --> 12:13.209
the murderous Declan Harp.

12:13.250 --> 12:16.584
You are officers of

12:13.250 --> 12:16.584
the Hudson's Bay Company

12:18.500 --> 12:21.792
and they have made fools

12:18.500 --> 12:21.792
of you gentlemen,

12:21.834 --> 12:23.834
every one of you!

12:25.500 --> 12:27.626
Isn't that so, Mr. Threadwell?

12:27.667 --> 12:29.334
(Waves lap)

12:30.375 --> 12:32.417
I want two things:

12:33.584 --> 12:35.751
total domination,

12:35.792 --> 12:38.083
meaning our competitors crushed,

12:38.125 --> 12:40.500
our monopoly restored,

12:40.542 --> 12:43.417
and I want Declan Harp

12:40.542 --> 12:43.417
on this ship alive.

12:46.834 --> 12:48.500
(Footsteps thud)

12:50.209 --> 12:53.667
Oh yes, how did

12:50.209 --> 12:53.667
Mr. Threadwell die?

12:56.459 --> 12:57.876
Anyone?

12:57.918 --> 13:01.959
♪♪♪

13:02.000 --> 13:03.792
- He was depressed, sir.

13:03.834 --> 13:05.918
Couldn't bear the trials

13:03.834 --> 13:05.918
of the New World.

13:05.959 --> 13:08.542
Took his own life, the coward.

13:08.584 --> 13:10.042
- (Chuckle) Good.

13:12.083 --> 13:13.417
(Wheezy chuckle)

13:13.459 --> 13:15.042
Very good.

13:16.125 --> 13:17.876
(Water laps gently)

13:17.918 --> 13:20.959
Coffin: They're called

13:17.918 --> 13:20.959
the Black Wolf Company.

13:21.000 --> 13:24.000
They've been undercutting

13:21.000 --> 13:24.000
English businesses,

13:24.042 --> 13:26.542
murdering English soldiers.

13:26.584 --> 13:28.834
- His men, who are they?

13:28.876 --> 13:30.834
- Mostly Metis and Scots.

13:32.042 --> 13:33.584
(Deep inhale)

13:33.626 --> 13:35.709
The woman is Ojibwe.

13:35.751 --> 13:37.667
The Canoes are full

13:35.751 --> 13:37.667
of trade goods.

13:37.709 --> 13:40.792
My guess is we're on our way

13:37.709 --> 13:40.792
to the Lake Walkers.

13:40.834 --> 13:43.500
I suspect Harp wants

13:40.834 --> 13:43.500
their trade,

13:43.542 --> 13:46.083
along with everyone else.

13:46.125 --> 13:48.709
- Do you think he's gonna

13:46.125 --> 13:48.709
kill us?

13:48.751 --> 13:51.292
- I'm not optimistic,

13:51.334 --> 13:54.125
but I'm betting you'd go first.

13:54.167 --> 13:55.626
(Low hum of chatter)

13:55.667 --> 13:58.083
(Footsteps crunch on gravel)

13:59.626 --> 14:00.709
(Fire crackles)

14:02.083 --> 14:03.959
- (Inhales sharply)

14:04.000 --> 14:05.626
Thank you kindly.

14:07.042 --> 14:09.125
- Thank you. I'm starved.

14:09.167 --> 14:11.083
(Chewing sounds)

14:12.876 --> 14:15.250
This is the tastiest piece

14:12.876 --> 14:15.250
of whatever this is

14:15.292 --> 14:17.209
I've ever tasted.

14:17.250 --> 14:19.167
(Waves lap)

14:19.209 --> 14:20.709
What's your name?

14:21.918 --> 14:23.876
I-I'm Michael, Michael Smyth,

14:23.918 --> 14:26.000
but you probably

14:23.918 --> 14:26.000
know that already.

14:26.042 --> 14:29.459
- Michael, take the hint,

14:26.042 --> 14:29.459
stop talking.

14:29.500 --> 14:31.042
(Fire crackles)

14:31.083 --> 14:32.751
(Howl in the distance)

14:33.959 --> 14:35.918
- Thanks for the food.

14:35.959 --> 14:37.292
(Receding footsteps)

14:37.334 --> 14:39.083
- Scares the...

14:39.125 --> 14:40.918
shit out of me, that one.

14:41.918 --> 14:44.626
- I don't think she's the one

14:41.918 --> 14:44.626
you need to be worryin' about.

14:44.667 --> 14:46.584
(Fire crackles)

14:46.626 --> 14:47.709
(Footsteps crunch)

14:47.751 --> 14:49.876
(Muted chatter

14:47.751 --> 14:49.876
of patrons inside)

14:49.918 --> 14:52.083
(Patrons chatter

14:49.918 --> 14:52.083
and laugh loudly)

14:52.125 --> 14:54.083
(Flame sizzles)

14:54.125 --> 14:56.042
(Candle holder thuds)

14:56.083 --> 14:57.250
(Footsteps thud)

14:58.334 --> 15:00.125
(Liquor pours)

15:01.125 --> 15:03.167
- Ma'am.

15:03.209 --> 15:05.000
(Cork pops, liquor sloshes)

15:05.042 --> 15:06.626
Do you never have one yourself?

15:06.667 --> 15:08.375
(Liquor flows)

15:08.417 --> 15:11.584
- How did you come

15:08.417 --> 15:11.584
to be on that ship?

15:11.626 --> 15:13.125
(Liquor flows)

15:13.167 --> 15:16.209
Lord Benton plucked you

15:13.167 --> 15:16.209
from a London whorehouse?

15:16.250 --> 15:18.792
Made you part of his "staff"?

15:18.834 --> 15:21.125
- My debt to Lord Benton

15:18.834 --> 15:21.125
is paid.

15:21.167 --> 15:23.959
(Cork squeaks)

15:21.167 --> 15:23.959
- Don't be naive, girl,

15:24.000 --> 15:25.918
your debt will never be paid.

15:25.959 --> 15:28.542
- Miss Emberly! There's

15:25.959 --> 15:28.542
something you need to see.

15:28.584 --> 15:30.125
- Mind the bar.

15:30.167 --> 15:33.292
♪♪♪

15:33.334 --> 15:35.626
Mary: I was coming out to fetch

15:33.334 --> 15:35.626
a wheel of cheese and sausage,

15:35.667 --> 15:37.918
and when I got here

15:35.667 --> 15:37.918
the lock was broken.

15:37.959 --> 15:39.918
You're not gonna like

15:37.959 --> 15:39.918
what I found inside.

15:39.959 --> 15:42.709
♪♪♪

15:42.751 --> 15:44.334
(Lock clanks)

15:44.375 --> 15:46.584
- (Singing drunkenly)

15:44.375 --> 15:46.584
Hi ho dee...

15:46.626 --> 15:49.709
(Approaching footsteps)

15:49.751 --> 15:51.250
- Cedric Brown!

15:51.292 --> 15:53.584
What the hell have you done,

15:51.292 --> 15:53.584
you drunken toe rag?

15:53.626 --> 15:55.167
- Grace Emberly!

15:55.209 --> 15:56.792
You're a fucking goddess!

15:56.834 --> 15:58.876
- Who's the boy?

15:58.918 --> 16:01.709
- I'm securing me

15:58.918 --> 16:01.709
and my brothers' future.

16:01.751 --> 16:03.792
- Do your brothers

16:01.751 --> 16:03.792
know what you've done?

16:03.834 --> 16:06.709
- Na, but they're gonna

16:03.834 --> 16:06.709
be fuckin' proud of me.

16:06.751 --> 16:08.792
- You fool, if this boy dies

16:08.834 --> 16:11.709
your brothers are gonna

16:08.834 --> 16:11.709
murder you!

16:11.751 --> 16:13.709
Look at his dress!

16:11.751 --> 16:13.709
Do you realize who he is?!

16:13.751 --> 16:15.584
Cedric: Damn right. He's Kitchi,

16:15.626 --> 16:17.584
grandson of the Chief

16:15.626 --> 16:17.584
of the Lake Walkers.

16:17.626 --> 16:19.709
- The wound's infected.

16:17.626 --> 16:19.709
Mary, deal with this.

16:19.751 --> 16:21.083
- What am I supposed

16:19.751 --> 16:21.083
to do with him?

16:21.125 --> 16:23.292
- Take him out,

16:21.125 --> 16:23.292
get him some coffee.

16:23.334 --> 16:24.792
(Hurried footsteps thud)

16:24.834 --> 16:26.667
- (Spits) Come on then.

16:26.709 --> 16:28.459
(Bottle clanks)

16:28.500 --> 16:31.209
- Where are you taking me,

16:28.500 --> 16:31.209
ya pretty little thing?

16:33.709 --> 16:35.751
(Door squeaks open)

16:33.709 --> 16:35.751
- Hold on there, laddie.

16:35.792 --> 16:37.626
(Door squeaks shut)

16:37.667 --> 16:41.209
♪♪♪

16:41.250 --> 16:44.042
(Birds chirp, rooster crow,

16:41.250 --> 16:44.042
sheep bleat)

16:44.083 --> 16:46.751
Emberly: His fever broke

16:44.083 --> 16:46.751
in the night.

16:46.792 --> 16:48.667
You got lucky, Cedric.

16:50.042 --> 16:51.959
- Fuck that.

16:52.000 --> 16:53.918
He wasna that bad.

16:53.959 --> 16:56.042
- How do you possibly think

16:53.959 --> 16:56.042
this can help you?

16:56.083 --> 16:58.709
- Force the Lake Walkers

16:56.083 --> 16:58.709
to trade with us.

16:58.751 --> 17:01.876
Fear is stronger than trust

16:58.751 --> 17:01.876
in my experience.

17:01.918 --> 17:03.459
(Slurps)

17:03.500 --> 17:06.500
- You're in for a rude

17:03.500 --> 17:06.500
awakening, you dolt.

17:06.542 --> 17:08.751
Cedric: Fuckin' terrible coffee.

17:08.792 --> 17:10.542
How about a little nip

17:08.792 --> 17:10.542
of somethin'?

17:10.584 --> 17:12.459
Emberly: I'd heard you were

17:10.584 --> 17:12.459
in collapse,

17:12.500 --> 17:14.542
you and your brothers, bankrupt.

17:15.709 --> 17:17.459
- We're pursuing an investor.

17:17.500 --> 17:19.125
- In Montreal?

17:19.167 --> 17:21.667
- Yeah. Where do you keep

17:19.167 --> 17:21.667
the brandy?

17:21.709 --> 17:22.959
(Footsteps thud)

17:23.959 --> 17:25.626
- Is he a fellow Scot?

17:25.667 --> 17:27.000
- An American.

17:27.042 --> 17:28.834
Rich as fuck, buckets of cash.

17:28.876 --> 17:30.751
Won't be long, you'll see.

17:30.792 --> 17:32.792
Brown Brothers back on top.

17:32.834 --> 17:34.626
(Liquor pours)

17:34.667 --> 17:36.542
- Aye, that's my girl.

17:36.584 --> 17:38.209
Oh, don't be shy.

17:38.250 --> 17:40.292
(Liquor pours)

17:43.459 --> 17:46.375
- And what's his name,

17:43.459 --> 17:46.375
this American?

17:46.417 --> 17:48.250
- Oh. Samuel Grant.

17:49.375 --> 17:51.167
He's a wee bit of a cocksucker,

17:51.209 --> 17:52.959
but doesn't na matter.

17:53.000 --> 17:55.292
Long as he fuckin' pays.

17:55.334 --> 17:56.792
(Slurps)

17:56.834 --> 17:59.250
♪♪♪

17:59.292 --> 18:00.834
(Swords clank)

18:00.876 --> 18:02.500
- Ah! (Door squeaks open)

18:02.542 --> 18:04.000
(Swords clank)

18:04.042 --> 18:06.167
Butler: Monsieur,

18:04.042 --> 18:06.167
s'il vous plait

18:07.500 --> 18:10.375
les freres Brown,

18:07.500 --> 18:10.375
Malcolm et Douglas,

18:10.417 --> 18:12.459
la Low Riviere Companie.

18:12.500 --> 18:14.083
- (Scoffs)

18:14.125 --> 18:17.083
That sounds a lot better when

18:14.125 --> 18:17.083
it's not in fuckin' French!

18:17.125 --> 18:19.125
No offence.

18:17.125 --> 18:19.125
(Door shuts)

18:19.167 --> 18:23.292
- Mr. Grant, we appreciate you

18:19.167 --> 18:23.292
taking the time to see us.

18:23.334 --> 18:25.292
As you may know, sir,

18:25.334 --> 18:26.918
we are highly successful

18:26.959 --> 18:29.209
procurers of beaver pelts

18:26.959 --> 18:29.209
from the wilderness.

18:29.250 --> 18:31.250
The Low River Company

18:29.250 --> 18:31.250
has a stellar track record--

18:31.292 --> 18:33.918
- We're expanding,

18:31.292 --> 18:33.918
moving north to the Bay.

18:33.959 --> 18:36.334
- We are on the brink of

18:33.959 --> 18:36.334
a stunningly lucrative

18:36.375 --> 18:38.876
trade agreement--

18:36.375 --> 18:38.876
- With the Lake Walker people,

18:38.918 --> 18:40.125
the Eastern Cree,

18:40.167 --> 18:41.959
who trade on behalf of further

18:42.000 --> 18:44.334
untold numbers of Cree

18:42.000 --> 18:44.334
to the West,

18:44.375 --> 18:46.125
and you need a buyer,

18:46.167 --> 18:48.125
someone who will receive

18:46.167 --> 18:48.125
your pelts.

18:48.167 --> 18:49.876
But gentlemen,

18:49.918 --> 18:52.834
I know you are in massive debt

18:52.876 --> 18:56.334
and are on the brink

18:52.876 --> 18:56.334
of total ruin.

18:56.375 --> 18:59.334
Moving pelts through the

18:56.375 --> 18:59.334
wilderness is very expensive.

18:59.375 --> 19:01.751
Portaging from

18:59.375 --> 19:01.751
waterway to waterway.

19:01.792 --> 19:03.834
Then of course you have

19:01.792 --> 19:03.834
to throw in

19:03.876 --> 19:05.334
the cost of trade goods,

19:05.375 --> 19:07.792
so you need more than a buyer.

19:05.375 --> 19:07.792
You need an investor.

19:07.834 --> 19:09.959
- Cash, aye. Up front.

19:07.834 --> 19:09.959
That's why we're here.

19:10.000 --> 19:12.334
- I thought there were three

19:10.000 --> 19:12.334
of you here in Montreal.

19:12.375 --> 19:15.292
A brother, Cecil, is it?

19:12.375 --> 19:15.292
- Cedric.

19:15.334 --> 19:17.375
- He's up North

19:15.334 --> 19:17.375
with the Lake Walkers.

19:17.417 --> 19:18.792
He's keeping them happy until--

19:18.834 --> 19:20.834
- Until with your assurance,

19:18.834 --> 19:20.834
Mr. Grant,

19:20.876 --> 19:22.042
we can close this deal.

19:22.083 --> 19:24.209
- And we can all get

19:22.083 --> 19:24.209
fuckin' rich!

19:24.250 --> 19:25.918
(Laughing)

19:27.209 --> 19:30.667
Grant: I hope he knows his

19:27.209 --> 19:30.667
business, your brother.

19:30.709 --> 19:33.918
There are many companies

19:30.709 --> 19:33.918
vying for Lake Walker trade

19:33.959 --> 19:35.459
and one wrong move--

19:35.500 --> 19:38.334
- All he has to do is

19:35.500 --> 19:38.334
bring gifts and smile.

19:38.375 --> 19:41.167
He might be a bit thick,

19:38.375 --> 19:41.167
but he'll get the job done.

19:41.209 --> 19:45.083
♪♪♪

19:45.125 --> 19:48.792
- I assume you've brought

19:45.125 --> 19:48.792
some sort of proposal?

19:48.834 --> 19:50.417
(Fingers strum)

19:51.584 --> 19:53.709
- You saw him yourself?

19:53.751 --> 19:55.876
- Yes, sir.

19:53.751 --> 19:55.876
Inside the storehouse

19:55.918 --> 19:57.417
there was a drunk Scottish man.

19:57.459 --> 19:59.834
She called him Cedric.

19:57.459 --> 19:59.834
- Cedric Brown?

19:59.876 --> 20:02.918
- He had a prisoner with him,

19:59.876 --> 20:02.918
a young native boy, Kitchi.

20:02.959 --> 20:04.834
I heard 'em say

20:02.959 --> 20:04.834
he was the grandson

20:04.876 --> 20:07.042
of the Lake Walker Chief.

20:07.083 --> 20:17.083
♪♪♪

20:18.250 --> 20:20.375
- Kneel.

20:28.959 --> 20:30.209
(Coin clinks)

20:32.209 --> 20:33.417
(Bones crunch)

20:33.459 --> 20:35.167
Imogen: (Grimaces in pain)

20:35.209 --> 20:38.626
- You will continue,

20:35.209 --> 20:38.626
eyes and ears open.

20:38.667 --> 20:40.667
- Yes, mi'lord!

20:40.709 --> 20:42.584
(Gasps in pain)

20:45.042 --> 20:47.000
(Running footsteps)

20:47.042 --> 20:48.918
(Door opens and shuts)

20:51.209 --> 20:52.918
- The grandson of the Chief.

20:52.959 --> 20:55.083
- The Lake Walkers despise us.

20:55.125 --> 20:58.209
Threadwell was cheating them

20:58.250 --> 21:00.459
and they are shrewd,

21:00.500 --> 21:04.250
but they also represent

21:00.500 --> 21:04.250
an enormous amount of trade.

21:05.417 --> 21:08.000
This boy would provide

21:05.417 --> 21:08.000
a superb incentive

21:08.042 --> 21:09.918
to restore ties,

21:11.167 --> 21:13.667
and bring the Company

21:11.167 --> 21:13.667
back real profit.

21:13.709 --> 21:15.125
- Not to mention...

21:16.167 --> 21:18.626
it would no doubt

21:16.167 --> 21:18.626
piss off Declan Harp.

21:18.667 --> 21:21.375
- You will be discreet.

21:21.417 --> 21:24.083
And Chesterfield,

21:24.125 --> 21:26.500
don't fail me again.

21:26.542 --> 21:36.083
♪♪♪

21:36.125 --> 21:38.167
(Door opens with

21:36.125 --> 21:38.167
a clattering bang)

21:38.209 --> 21:40.042
- Where is he?

21:40.083 --> 21:41.417
Where's the boy?!

21:41.459 --> 21:43.000
- What do you think

21:41.459 --> 21:43.000
you're doin'?

21:43.042 --> 21:45.167
Take him.

21:43.042 --> 21:45.167
- You leave him be, he is sick!

21:46.500 --> 21:48.167
(Violent bang)

21:48.209 --> 21:50.209
- You were going to keep

21:48.209 --> 21:50.209
this from me?

21:50.250 --> 21:52.000
- Of course not.

21:52.042 --> 21:53.584
- (Seething breaths)

21:53.626 --> 21:57.167
- I was trying to protect him

21:53.626 --> 21:57.167
from the stupid Brown Brothers.

21:57.209 --> 22:00.709
I wasna hiding him

21:57.209 --> 22:00.709
from you or Benton.

22:00.751 --> 22:02.334
Now calm down.

22:03.667 --> 22:06.042
- (Calming breaths)

22:06.083 --> 22:07.626
- (Relieved exhale)

22:09.125 --> 22:11.083
(Steadied breathing)

22:11.125 --> 22:13.334
- We need to work together,

22:11.125 --> 22:13.334
you and I.

22:13.375 --> 22:14.542
-(Steadied breathing)

22:14.584 --> 22:16.959
- So why don't you leave

22:14.584 --> 22:16.959
boy in here,

22:17.000 --> 22:18.959
let me take care of him.

22:19.000 --> 22:20.417
(Door opens)

22:20.459 --> 22:22.375
(Door shuts)

22:24.709 --> 22:26.751
Cedric: What the fuck's

22:24.709 --> 22:26.751
goin' on?

22:26.792 --> 22:30.584
♪♪♪

22:30.626 --> 22:33.000
- Hello, Cedric.

22:33.042 --> 22:35.375
I don't believe we've met.

22:35.417 --> 22:37.375
- Who the fuck are you?

22:37.417 --> 22:38.709
(Blade clinks, violent thrusts)

22:38.751 --> 22:39.751
(Pained grunts)

22:39.792 --> 22:41.042
(Wet knife slice)

22:41.083 --> 22:42.751
(Choked gasps)

22:44.417 --> 22:46.417
(Violent thud)

22:44.417 --> 22:46.417
(Liquor splashes)

22:46.459 --> 22:48.250
(Dying shaky gasps)

22:51.000 --> 22:53.000
(Children giggle playfully)

22:53.042 --> 22:54.459
(Low hum of chatter)

22:55.542 --> 22:58.584
♪♪♪

22:58.626 --> 23:00.751
(Guns clatter)

23:00.792 --> 23:04.417
♪♪♪

23:04.459 --> 23:06.125
(Lanterns clink)

23:07.375 --> 23:09.250
Harp: We are honored

23:07.375 --> 23:09.250
to be here.

23:09.292 --> 23:12.459
These gifts extend our wishes

23:09.292 --> 23:12.459
for your prosperity.

23:12.500 --> 23:14.542
(Fire crackles)

23:14.584 --> 23:15.584
(Waves lap)

23:15.626 --> 23:18.042
- (in Cree) Kia, Kia. Esto.

23:19.876 --> 23:21.876
Coffin: Jesus,

23:19.876 --> 23:21.876
I can't take this...

23:21.918 --> 23:23.125
(Breathing hard)

23:23.167 --> 23:24.709
the anticipation.

23:24.751 --> 23:26.959
Every breath I take

23:24.751 --> 23:26.959
I think that's it,

23:27.000 --> 23:29.250
that's the last one!

23:27.000 --> 23:29.250
The journey's over!

23:29.292 --> 23:32.167
If you're gonna kill us then

23:29.292 --> 23:32.167
kill us for the love of God!

23:32.209 --> 23:34.083
Michael: Ignore him.

23:34.125 --> 23:36.292
Nervous disposition,

23:34.125 --> 23:36.292
normally he'd be drunk.

23:37.334 --> 23:39.209
(Fire crackles)

23:39.250 --> 23:41.417
So these are the Lake Walkers?

23:41.459 --> 23:43.250
Samoset: The woman is Kamenna.

23:43.292 --> 23:44.959
She is Okimaw.

23:45.000 --> 23:47.250
She executes the will

23:45.000 --> 23:47.250
of the people.

23:47.292 --> 23:50.542
Givin' her gifts

23:47.292 --> 23:50.542
is a sign of respect.

23:50.584 --> 23:52.834
You two are included.

23:52.876 --> 23:54.584
- What's that now?

23:54.626 --> 23:56.167
- Gifts?

23:56.209 --> 23:58.334
Coffin: Oh, Jesus Christ

23:58.375 --> 24:00.209
Almighty God in heaven.

24:00.250 --> 24:02.209
(Panicked breathing)

24:02.250 --> 24:05.834
♪♪♪

24:05.876 --> 24:08.000
- The muskets that we brought

24:05.876 --> 24:08.000
are well made.

24:08.042 --> 24:10.209
flints that won't freeze

24:08.042 --> 24:10.209
in the snow.

24:10.250 --> 24:12.417
- You've been killing

24:10.250 --> 24:12.417
English soldiers.

24:12.459 --> 24:15.209
We hear you're consumed

24:12.459 --> 24:15.209
by a blood rage.

24:15.250 --> 24:16.584
(Fire crackles)

24:16.626 --> 24:20.250
- I have enemies, yes,

24:16.626 --> 24:20.250
but I'm consumed by nothing.

24:20.500 --> 24:22.417
Lies!

24:22.459 --> 24:24.876
He is the son

24:22.459 --> 24:24.876
of an Irish trapper.

24:24.918 --> 24:27.292
So his mother was Cree,

24:27.334 --> 24:29.334
it makes no difference.

24:29.375 --> 24:32.751
He's a European.

24:32.792 --> 24:34.375
I am not the English!

24:36.667 --> 24:37.709
I will be fair Okimaw.

24:39.792 --> 24:40.792
I will honour your people.

24:42.876 --> 24:45.334
- You have come

24:42.876 --> 24:45.334
a great distance,

24:45.375 --> 24:49.292
but now's not the time to be

24:45.375 --> 24:49.292
talking about trade.

24:49.334 --> 24:51.500
(Fire crackles)

24:52.834 --> 24:54.209
- Have I offended you?

24:54.250 --> 24:55.626
Kamenna: No.

24:55.667 --> 24:57.042
(Distressed sigh)

24:57.083 --> 24:59.375
My grandson's been taken,

24:59.417 --> 25:01.417
his friend's been shot.

25:02.834 --> 25:04.542
- By whom?

25:04.584 --> 25:06.083
(Fire Crackles)

25:06.125 --> 25:07.584
- (Grunts)

25:07.626 --> 25:10.042
- Your grandson,

25:07.626 --> 25:10.042
what is his name?

25:10.083 --> 25:12.125
- Kitchi.

25:12.167 --> 25:14.042
He's merely a boy.

25:14.083 --> 25:15.209
(Fire crackles)

25:15.250 --> 25:21.709
♪♪♪

25:21.751 --> 25:24.250
- I will make you this promise,

25:21.751 --> 25:24.250
Okimaw:

25:24.292 --> 25:25.959
if he is alive,

25:26.000 --> 25:28.000
I will find him.

25:28.042 --> 25:30.000
I will bring him home to you.

25:30.042 --> 25:31.626
My word is good.

25:31.667 --> 25:33.667
(Footsteps rustle

25:31.667 --> 25:33.667
in the foliage)

25:33.709 --> 25:35.751
Coffin: They're going

25:33.709 --> 25:35.751
to leave us here!

25:35.792 --> 25:37.751
God help us. They're actually

25:35.792 --> 25:37.751
gonna do it,

25:37.792 --> 25:39.792
they're gonna paddle off

25:37.792 --> 25:39.792
and leave us here!

25:39.834 --> 25:42.167
- Would you shut up!

25:39.834 --> 25:42.167
- It was Benton who did this,

25:42.209 --> 25:44.209
I'm sure of it.

25:42.209 --> 25:44.209
- He's a fool.

25:44.250 --> 25:46.751
He thinks he can intimidate

25:44.250 --> 25:46.751
these people into trade.

25:46.792 --> 25:49.542
- You think the boy's alive?

25:46.792 --> 25:49.542
- He's no good to anyone dead.

25:49.584 --> 25:51.626
Samoset: I've seen the English

25:49.584 --> 25:51.626
do this before.

25:51.667 --> 25:53.751
Take a prisoner and then

25:51.667 --> 25:53.751
threaten to hang them

25:53.792 --> 25:55.167
to motivate trade negotiations.

25:55.209 --> 25:58.292
- I don't think it was Benton.

25:55.209 --> 25:58.292
Dimanche: Be quiet, boy.

25:58.334 --> 26:01.209
- No. Let him speak.

26:01.250 --> 26:03.250
- All he thinks about is you,

26:03.292 --> 26:05.417
is killing you.

26:05.459 --> 26:08.375
How many other companies wanna

26:05.459 --> 26:08.375
trade with the Lake Walkers?

26:08.417 --> 26:10.250
Any one of 'em could have

26:08.417 --> 26:10.250
taken the boy.

26:10.292 --> 26:13.375
- Well, we're going to be

26:10.292 --> 26:13.375
the ones that find Kitchi.

26:13.417 --> 26:15.584
It's the only way

26:13.417 --> 26:15.584
to secure their trade.

26:15.626 --> 26:16.876
We're going to Fort James.

26:16.918 --> 26:19.459
- Excellent choice!

26:16.918 --> 26:19.459
Right behind you.

26:19.500 --> 26:21.834
- It seems you're still with us.

26:24.667 --> 26:26.709
(Patrons laugh

26:24.667 --> 26:26.709
and chatter loudly)

26:26.751 --> 26:28.626
(Bottle clanks loudly)

26:26.751 --> 26:28.626
- Grace...

26:28.667 --> 26:30.500
(Fiddle playing)

26:31.626 --> 26:33.459
(Boisterous chatter, laughter)

26:33.500 --> 26:35.292
(Approaching footsteps)

26:35.334 --> 26:37.209
(Liquor pours, bottle thumps)

26:38.209 --> 26:40.167
- He wasn't a friend of yours,

26:38.209 --> 26:40.167
I hope?

26:40.209 --> 26:41.584
- Cedric?

26:41.626 --> 26:43.792
A friend, no.

26:43.834 --> 26:45.375
A customer, yes.

26:46.500 --> 26:49.500
Interesting approach you have

26:46.500 --> 26:49.500
to problem solving.

26:49.542 --> 26:50.959
- Does it offend you?

26:51.000 --> 26:52.542
- Quite the opposite.

26:52.584 --> 26:55.167
I respect a man whose

26:52.584 --> 26:55.167
actions are decisive.

26:55.209 --> 26:56.584
(Fiddle playing)

26:57.876 --> 27:00.375
- The boy's alive.

26:57.876 --> 27:00.375
He's being cared for.

27:00.417 --> 27:02.626
- Is that what you came here

27:00.417 --> 27:02.626
to tell me?

27:02.667 --> 27:04.042
(Fire crackles)

27:04.083 --> 27:07.500
Or have you given our

27:04.083 --> 27:07.500
partnership some thought?

27:07.542 --> 27:09.083
(Fiddle playing)

27:10.167 --> 27:12.834
- What precisely do you

27:10.167 --> 27:12.834
have in mind?

27:12.876 --> 27:15.375
- If I'm not mistaken,

27:15.417 --> 27:17.459
you control the movement

27:15.417 --> 27:17.459
of inventory,

27:17.500 --> 27:19.584
and when pelts come

27:17.500 --> 27:19.584
into the fort

27:19.626 --> 27:22.083
it's your responsibility

27:19.626 --> 27:22.083
to put them in lock-up.

27:22.125 --> 27:24.125
If, with each shipment,

27:25.209 --> 27:28.083
a couple of bundles

27:25.209 --> 27:28.083
of pelts were to be...

27:28.125 --> 27:30.167
diverted.

27:30.209 --> 27:33.751
- How exactly does this lead

27:30.209 --> 27:33.751
to me becoming Governor?

27:33.792 --> 27:35.834
- Well, if you want to be

27:33.792 --> 27:35.834
in charge around here,

27:35.876 --> 27:38.626
you'll need money

27:35.876 --> 27:38.626
and plenty of it.

27:38.667 --> 27:40.417
(Fire crackles)

27:40.459 --> 27:42.542
And more importantly...

27:42.584 --> 27:45.417
you'll need to discredit Lord

27:42.584 --> 27:45.417
Benton in the eyes of London.

27:45.459 --> 27:47.500
Profits are dwindling.

27:47.542 --> 27:49.751
He's losing control

27:47.542 --> 27:49.751
of the Company and the fort.

27:49.792 --> 27:51.876
- You best be careful.

27:51.918 --> 27:53.918
If those words got back

27:51.918 --> 27:53.918
to Lord Benton

27:53.959 --> 27:56.334
he'd murder you.

27:56.375 --> 27:59.292
As you know,

27:56.375 --> 27:59.292
there's one among you.

28:01.167 --> 28:03.167
- Imogen. I'm aware.

28:03.209 --> 28:05.042
I can handle her.

28:05.083 --> 28:06.918
- Of course you can.

28:08.375 --> 28:10.876
- The native boy needs medicine.

28:10.918 --> 28:13.459
I'd see to that if I were you.

28:14.709 --> 28:16.584
- Should we drink to it then?

28:16.626 --> 28:19.459
- Later, perhaps. I'm workin'.

28:20.959 --> 28:22.375
- (Slurps)

28:23.500 --> 28:24.584
(Ominous music)

28:25.751 --> 28:27.417
(Cup thumps down)

28:27.459 --> 28:29.167
(Retreating footsteps)

28:30.209 --> 28:33.459
- Follow him. See where he goes.

28:30.209 --> 28:33.459
(Door shuts)

28:33.500 --> 28:35.584
I want to know where

28:33.500 --> 28:35.584
he's taken the boy.

28:35.626 --> 28:41.792
♪♪♪

28:41.834 --> 28:43.792
(Fire crackles)

28:43.834 --> 28:45.459
(Marching footsteps crunch)

28:45.500 --> 28:55.500
♪♪♪

28:55.542 --> 28:57.250
- Stay by the fire.

28:57.292 --> 28:58.959
Over here.

29:01.667 --> 29:04.167
(Footstep crunch in the gravel)

29:04.209 --> 29:05.459
(Door opens)

29:05.500 --> 29:07.667
(Patrons laugh

29:05.500 --> 29:07.667
and chatter loudly)

29:08.751 --> 29:11.459
(Loud overlapping chatter)

29:11.500 --> 29:12.709
(Door shuts)

29:12.751 --> 29:14.792
(Footsteps scuff)

29:14.834 --> 29:16.834
Emberly: Christ, Harp,

29:16.876 --> 29:18.959
it's not safe for you here.

29:20.834 --> 29:24.209
- I came to see you.

29:20.834 --> 29:24.209
(Liquor pours)

29:24.250 --> 29:26.626
(Liquor pours)

29:24.250 --> 29:26.626
(Bottle clanks)

29:28.959 --> 29:30.918
- Come on.

29:30.959 --> 29:33.751
(Patrons laugh

29:30.959 --> 29:33.751
and chatter loudly)

29:33.792 --> 29:36.500
(Chair rasps)

29:36.542 --> 29:38.459
- Grace, I need to talk to you.

29:38.500 --> 29:41.042
- Where have you been?

29:41.083 --> 29:42.667
Look at you.

29:44.209 --> 29:49.292
♪♪♪

29:49.334 --> 29:51.626
- I need information.

29:51.667 --> 29:54.167
- Are you serious?

29:54.209 --> 29:56.876
I've not seen you in months.

29:56.918 --> 29:59.125
- You give information

29:56.918 --> 29:59.125
to everyone else,

29:59.167 --> 30:01.709
now I need you to give me some.

30:03.000 --> 30:05.000
- Not for nothin' I won't.

30:05.042 --> 30:07.459
- This was a mistake.

30:05.042 --> 30:07.459
- No, wait!

30:10.500 --> 30:12.500
Tell me why you're here.

30:14.417 --> 30:16.500
Declan...

30:16.542 --> 30:21.000
♪♪♪

30:21.042 --> 30:22.792
- There's a Lake Walker boy

30:21.042 --> 30:22.792
named Kitchi.

30:22.834 --> 30:24.584
He was taken captive.

30:24.626 --> 30:26.709
Do you know anything about it?

30:27.792 --> 30:30.626
- He was here a few nights ago.

30:31.709 --> 30:33.667
- And?

30:33.709 --> 30:36.042
- Well, his wounds

30:33.709 --> 30:36.042
were festerin'.

30:36.083 --> 30:38.042
I kept him hidden here,

30:36.083 --> 30:38.042
took care of him

30:38.083 --> 30:40.834
until his fever broke.

30:38.083 --> 30:40.834
- And who brought him in?

30:40.876 --> 30:43.459
- Cedric Brown.

30:40.876 --> 30:43.459
He stole the boy.

30:43.500 --> 30:45.125
- Not Benton?

30:45.167 --> 30:46.876
- No, Cedric first.

30:48.751 --> 30:51.584
Then Benton's man Chesterfield

30:48.751 --> 30:51.584
came along and took him.

30:51.626 --> 30:53.792
- And where are they holdin'

30:51.626 --> 30:53.792
him now?

30:53.834 --> 30:55.500
Where's the boy?

30:55.542 --> 30:57.584
- Declan, you can't keep

30:55.542 --> 30:57.584
chasing Benton.

30:57.626 --> 30:59.542
- Where's the boy, Grace?

30:59.584 --> 31:01.751
- Look, I know you've been

30:59.584 --> 31:01.751
through hell,

31:01.792 --> 31:04.959
but going after Benton is never

31:01.792 --> 31:04.959
gonna bring your wife back.

31:05.000 --> 31:10.459
♪♪♪

31:10.500 --> 31:12.709
- Where is the boy?

31:12.751 --> 31:16.334
♪♪♪

31:16.375 --> 31:17.918
(Fire crackles)

31:17.959 --> 31:20.375
- Last night, maybe?

31:20.417 --> 31:22.584
The night before?

31:22.626 --> 31:24.626
Truthfully, I have no precise

31:22.626 --> 31:24.626
knowledge

31:24.667 --> 31:27.000
of when it occurred

31:24.667 --> 31:27.000
or the cause.

31:27.042 --> 31:31.167
The fear perhaps,

31:27.042 --> 31:31.167
the lack of drink,

31:31.209 --> 31:33.542
first time I've been sober

31:31.209 --> 31:33.542
in seven months,

31:33.584 --> 31:34.792
(Fire crackles)

31:34.834 --> 31:36.959
but the point is,

31:34.834 --> 31:36.959
my young friend,

31:37.000 --> 31:39.375
a miracle has occurred!

31:39.417 --> 31:41.584
God has arrived in the

31:39.417 --> 31:41.584
wilderness and entered me!

31:41.626 --> 31:44.250
(Chuckling) I am full

31:41.626 --> 31:44.250
of the Holy Spirit!

31:44.292 --> 31:45.709
I am a new man!

31:45.751 --> 31:48.250
My sins are behind me, Michael.

31:48.292 --> 31:50.292
I am reborn.

31:50.334 --> 31:51.959
(Door opens)

31:52.000 --> 31:53.667
(Footsteps thud)

31:53.709 --> 31:57.709
- Brilliant. When does God

31:53.709 --> 31:57.709
tell you to shut up?

31:57.751 --> 32:00.334
Man: (Grunts drunkenly)

32:00.375 --> 32:01.959
(Liquor sloshes in bottle)

32:03.042 --> 32:04.959
- Look at this poor soul now.

32:05.000 --> 32:07.334
This is my mission, right here!

32:05.000 --> 32:07.334
My son!

32:07.375 --> 32:09.667
- Coffin!

32:07.375 --> 32:09.667
- If I might speak to you!

32:09.709 --> 32:11.125
Samoset: Let him go.

32:11.167 --> 32:13.083
He won't be hard to find.

32:13.125 --> 32:15.250
(Fire crackles)

32:15.292 --> 32:16.834
(Door opens)

32:19.876 --> 32:21.584
- They're back.

32:25.375 --> 32:28.125
- Governor's House,

32:25.375 --> 32:28.125
edge of town.

32:28.167 --> 32:30.334
(Brush rustles quietly)

32:30.375 --> 32:35.375
♪♪♪

32:35.417 --> 32:37.417
- That's where they're

32:35.417 --> 32:37.417
keeping the boy?

32:37.459 --> 32:39.000
Do we know where? What room?

32:39.042 --> 32:40.167
- No.

32:40.209 --> 32:41.584
Samoset: Cellar maybe?

32:41.626 --> 32:43.542
He'll be tied up, under guard.

32:43.584 --> 32:45.334
- How many soldiers?

32:45.375 --> 32:47.542
- Ten, fifteen.

32:45.375 --> 32:47.542
- At least.

32:47.584 --> 32:49.000
- Look.

32:49.042 --> 32:52.626
♪♪♪

32:52.667 --> 32:53.876
(Door opens)

32:55.417 --> 32:57.375
(Lanterns clatter)

32:57.417 --> 32:59.000
(Footsteps thud)

33:00.417 --> 33:02.083
- We use knives.

33:02.125 --> 33:04.500
Go room by room,

33:04.542 --> 33:06.375
slit their throats

33:04.542 --> 33:06.375
as they sleep.

33:06.417 --> 33:09.000
- Too dangerous.

33:06.417 --> 33:09.000
We're too outnumbered.

33:09.042 --> 33:11.459
We should wait, keep watch,

33:11.500 --> 33:13.667
see if we can catch

33:11.500 --> 33:13.667
a glimpse of Kitchi.

33:13.709 --> 33:15.667
- I have an idea.

33:13.709 --> 33:15.667
- Quiet, boy.

33:15.709 --> 33:17.375
- No, go on.

33:17.417 --> 33:19.292
I walk through the front door.

33:19.334 --> 33:20.876
I'm returnin' from the wild,

33:20.918 --> 33:22.876
I'm there to see Lord Benton.

33:22.918 --> 33:25.209
I'll tell him that I've worked

33:22.918 --> 33:25.209
my way into your trust

33:25.250 --> 33:27.083
but I don't know much,

33:27.125 --> 33:30.000
and you're expecting me back

33:27.125 --> 33:30.000
in the morning.

33:30.042 --> 33:31.918
- And in the meantime?

33:31.959 --> 33:34.125
- I'm desperate for a proper

33:31.959 --> 33:34.125
bed and a decent meal.

33:34.167 --> 33:36.751
I'll ask if I can stay

33:34.167 --> 33:36.751
the night.

33:36.792 --> 33:39.083
When's all is quiet,

33:36.792 --> 33:39.083
they're all asleep...

33:39.125 --> 33:41.500
I let you in.

33:41.542 --> 33:43.250
- It's too risky.

33:43.292 --> 33:45.417
We don't know what

33:43.292 --> 33:45.417
he'll say to Benton.

33:45.459 --> 33:47.792
This could be lies he's telling

33:45.459 --> 33:47.792
to get us killed!

33:56.834 --> 33:59.250
- All right, Michael Smyth.

33:59.292 --> 34:02.500
Let's see how you do

33:59.292 --> 34:02.500
when the wind picks up.

34:03.959 --> 34:05.792
(Rocks clink)

34:05.834 --> 34:15.334
♪♪♪

34:15.375 --> 34:17.167
Michael: Whoa whoa.

34:17.209 --> 34:18.250
My name's Michael Smyth.

34:18.292 --> 34:20.334
Lord Benton's expecting me.

34:20.375 --> 34:21.834
(Fire crackles)

34:22.876 --> 34:24.042
(Door opens)

34:24.083 --> 34:26.083
- Go on, sir.

34:26.125 --> 34:28.667
- I fear he will betray us.

34:28.709 --> 34:30.209
(Door shuts)

34:31.876 --> 34:34.459
(Knock at door)

34:31.876 --> 34:34.459
(Door opens)

34:34.500 --> 34:36.751
- Begging your pardon, sir.

34:37.792 --> 34:40.292
Would you like me to--

34:37.792 --> 34:40.292
- Out.

34:40.334 --> 34:41.751
(Door shuts)

34:43.918 --> 34:45.417
- Lord Benton.

34:45.459 --> 34:48.250
- Well, the stowaway returns.

34:48.292 --> 34:50.292
I'd assumed you were

34:48.292 --> 34:50.292
gone for good.

34:50.334 --> 34:52.751
- I hope you know I didn't kill

34:50.334 --> 34:52.751
your man from the ship.

34:52.792 --> 34:53.918
- I couldn't care less.

34:53.959 --> 34:56.792
Have you made contact

34:53.959 --> 34:56.792
with Declan Harp?

34:56.834 --> 34:58.709
- Yes, sir.

34:58.751 --> 35:00.751
I've kept up my side

34:58.751 --> 35:00.751
of the bargain.

35:00.792 --> 35:02.792
Have you made contact

35:00.792 --> 35:02.792
with Clenna?

35:02.834 --> 35:04.584
- Harp has accepted you?

35:04.626 --> 35:06.584
- He threatens to kill

35:04.626 --> 35:06.584
me every day.

35:06.626 --> 35:08.834
I don't know how much longer

35:06.626 --> 35:08.834
I can keep this up.

35:08.876 --> 35:10.292
- How many men does he have?

35:10.334 --> 35:12.167
- I've seen 20,

35:10.334 --> 35:12.167
but there's many more,

35:12.209 --> 35:14.375
a hundred, possibly two.

35:14.417 --> 35:16.125
He's makin' alliances.

35:16.167 --> 35:17.417
He's plannin' one right now

35:17.459 --> 35:19.500
with the Cree tribe

35:17.459 --> 35:19.500
the Lake Walkers.

35:19.542 --> 35:22.542
- I see. What else?

35:19.542 --> 35:22.542
- That's all I know.

35:22.584 --> 35:24.209
- His camp?

35:24.250 --> 35:25.918
Michael: I haven't seen a camp.

35:25.959 --> 35:27.876
We're constantly on the move.

35:27.918 --> 35:29.125
To tell you the truth, my Lord,

35:29.167 --> 35:31.167
there's no one place

35:29.167 --> 35:31.167
you can find him.

35:31.209 --> 35:33.584
I told him I would steal

35:31.209 --> 35:33.584
some supplies

35:33.626 --> 35:35.542
from the fort here tonight.

35:35.584 --> 35:38.042
Perhaps you could help

35:35.584 --> 35:38.042
me with that, sir?

35:38.083 --> 35:39.709
I'm to return in the morning.

35:39.751 --> 35:43.417
- Return where?

35:39.751 --> 35:43.417
- The river.

35:43.459 --> 35:45.500
He, he'll send someone

35:43.459 --> 35:45.500
to meet me.

35:45.542 --> 35:47.584
He's beyond careful.

35:47.626 --> 35:49.459
- Yes, of course. Sit.

35:50.959 --> 35:52.334
- Sir, if I may ask

35:50.959 --> 35:52.334
about Clenna--

35:52.375 --> 35:56.375
- I secure your girl's safety

35:52.375 --> 35:56.375
when you deliver Harp.

35:59.209 --> 36:01.083
Now, please.

36:02.500 --> 36:04.417
You look dreadful,

36:04.459 --> 36:06.667
and you smell worse.

36:06.709 --> 36:07.959
(Liquor pours)

36:09.918 --> 36:11.209
(Bottle clanks down)

36:12.375 --> 36:24.626
♪♪♪

36:24.667 --> 36:26.918
You must be careful.

36:26.959 --> 36:28.918
Harp will charm you,

36:28.959 --> 36:30.918
persuade you to join his cause.

36:32.042 --> 36:35.125
You may even feel the bonds

36:32.042 --> 36:35.125
of friendship forming,

36:35.167 --> 36:37.167
but this is an illusion.

36:38.209 --> 36:41.334
The man cares only

36:38.209 --> 36:41.334
